The unit masks allow for counting various combinations of victim merit information. ICVal indicates the line may have been removed from the IC, DCVal indicates is was removed from the L1DC and UnusedPf indicates that the line was brought by a prefetch and was never brought into the L1. Note that the L2 is not notified when a line is removed from the IC, so ICVal is conservative; that is, if it is true, it means the line may be in the IC, but when it is false, the line is certainly not in the IC.
